<exercise checkit-seed="0013" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>P= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-2 &amp; 3 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 \\
-3 &amp; 6 &amp; 1 &amp; -5 \\
-2 &amp; 8 &amp; -1 &amp; -2
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>P^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
21 &amp; 7 &amp; -17 &amp; 4 \\
10 &amp; 3 &amp; -8 &amp; 2 \\
28 &amp; 8 &amp; -22 &amp; 5 \\
5 &amp; 1 &amp; -4 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

